en_284602_0	A group of Army personnel competent in Reality Based Self Defence (RBSD) martial art, attached to the Security Force Headquarters-East (SFHQ-E) conducted a demonstration for 3 Officers and 60 Other Ranks of the Security Force Headquarters - Mullaittivu (SFHQ-MLT) on 07 June 2018 in order to encourage them for the art.
en_284602_1	The event was held at the 23 Division Headquarters, Punani, in the presence of the General Officer Commanding 23 Division, Brigadier Chula Abenayaka.
en_284602_2	The Reality Based Self Defence (RBSD) course was carefully designed on the directions of the Commander, Security Forces - East (SF-E), Major General Santhusitha Pananwala with special focus on enhancing the capacity of men and women serving the Security Force Headquarters - East (SFHQ-E) to face any future security challenges.
en_284602_3	Reality Based Self Defence (RBSD) training module is pivotal for engagements and disengagements with aggressive crowds and individuals.
en_284602_4	These trained groups can be directed to collect information, intelligence-collecting, operations and strikes on the approval of relevant authorities.
en_284602_5	Accordingly, 23 Division has conducted 04 RBSD courses to date with the assistance of skilled and professional soldiers of the 1 Commando Regiment (CR).
